        <section>
            <h3>Important Instructions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>JSON Files</strong>: Should contain a single JSON array, with each product as a JSON object.
                    Each object must have the following keys: <code>product_name</code>, <code>description</code>,
                    <code>image_url</code>, <code>price</code>, <code>isbn</code>, <code>author</code>,
                    <code>category_id</code>, <code>pages</code>, <code>publisher</code>, <code>featured</code> (0 or
                    1), <code>trending</code> (0 or 1), and <code>new_release</code> (0 or 1).
                </li>
                <li><strong>CSV Files</strong>: First row must be headers with the exact field names (case-sensitive):
                    <code>product_name</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>image_url</code>, <code>price</code>,
                    <code>isbn</code>, <code>author</code>, <code>category_id</code>, <code>pages</code>,
                    <code>publisher</code>, <code>featured</code>, <code>trending</code>, <code>new_release</code>.
                    Subsequent rows must have product data separated by commas.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Text Files</strong>: Each product's data should be separated by a blank line. Each field
                    must be in the format: <code>attribute_name: attribute_value</code> (e.g.,
                    <code>product_name: The Great Gatsby</code>). Attribute names must match the JSON keys exactly.
                </li>
                <li>Ensure the <code>category_id</code> matches an existing category in your database.</li>
                <li><code>price</code> and <code>pages</code> must be numeric values.</li>
                <li><code>featured</code>, <code>trending</code>, and <code>new_release</code> should be either
                    <code>0</code> or <code>1</code>.
                </li>
                <li>Double-check your file format before uploading to avoid errors.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

